value.title: Mike Pence Brought Conservatives Home. What If They Don’t Need Him Anymore?
value.excerpt: Evangelical Christians were drawn to the vice president because he shared their values. But Trump’s style has made defiance of political norms, not a Pence specialty, seem appealing.

value.title: Trump's declassifying order won't erase his wrongdoing, Swalwell says
value.excerpt: Rep. Eric Swalwell calls Trump move a 'sloppy sleight of hand'

value.title: Trump allies, Republicans say American people 'deserve the truth,' praise declassification of Russia probe docs
value.excerpt: Top Republicans and allies of President Trump praised his move to declassify all documents related to the Russia investigation saying the “American people deserve the truth.”

value.title: New York Times editorial board endorses Biden
value.excerpt: The New York Times editorial board endorsed Joe Biden's White House bid on Tuesday, throwing its support behind the former vice president&nb

value.title: Trump says it'll be 'fast and easy' to confirm Amy Coney Barrett
value.excerpt: President Trump declared on Twitter Tuesday evening that the Senate battle to confirm Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court “will be fast and easy.”

value.title: Puerto Rico Gov. Wanda Vázquez Garced endorses Trump re-election bid
value.excerpt: Last month, the Trump administration unveiled a $13 billion aid package to help Puerto Rico in its ongoing recovery from Hurricane Maria.

value.title: Biden says United States is in a 'dangerous place' and calls for unity in Gettysburg speech
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden warned of the "cost of division" Tuesday in a speech in Gettysburg, Pennsylvania, delivering a call to turn past a moment he said is "neither good nor normal" and unify.

value.title: Biden vows not to allow ‘White supremacists to overturn the America of Lincoln’
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden made a forceful plea for national unity on Tuesday as he took aim at “extremist white supremacist groups menacing our communities.”

value.title: Biden in Gettysburg speech invokes Lincoln, calls for unity
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden delivered an impassioned plea for unity while invoking former President Lincoln during a speech in Gettysburg, Pa., on Tuesday, exactly four weeks before the election.

value.title: Fact check: Satirical post falsely claims Trump would be fine if he hadn't gotten tested
value.excerpt: A liberal commentator's Facebook post claims Trump would be fine if he didn't get tested, satirically referencing debunked claim about coronavirus.

value.title: Federal judge rejects Trump's efforts to curtail New Jersey vote-by-mail plans
value.excerpt: A federal judge in New Jersey on Tuesday rejected an attempt by President Donald Trump's campaign to curtail part of the state's vote-by-mail plan just weeks before Election Day.

value.title: Biden raises eyebrows after telling 'these beautiful young ladies' he wants to 'see them dancing when they're four years older'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has been raising eyebrows again with remarks he made to a group of "beautiful young ladies" during a campaign stop in Miami.

value.title: The Point: Donald Trump, dealmaker? Not so much.
value.excerpt: Donald Trump came to the White House promising that he would make deals the likes of which the country and the world never seen.

value.title: Pence team objects to plexiglass being installed for both candidates at VP debate
value.excerpt: Mike Pence does not want plexiglass barriers around him at the vice presidential debate against Kamala Harris on Wednesday, a top aide to the vice president told CNN on Tuesday, rebuffing an announcement from the Commission on Presidential debates that the dividers would be used to prevent the spread

value.title: Tim Kaine on What It’s Like to Debate Mike Pence
value.excerpt: Mr. Kaine, Hillary Clinton’s running mate in 2016, spoke to The Times about what lies ahead for Senator Kamala Harris at Wednesday’s V.P. debate.

value.title: Pence to vote in Indiana this week as state's early voting begins
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and second lady Karen Pence are expected to fly to Indiana Friday, to vote in person from the second family’s home state, as early voting kicked off Tuesday.

value.title: Hollywood-inspired ‘Trump’ sign pops up on mountainside above California freeway
value.excerpt: A towering, Hollywood-esque Trump sign briefly appeared above California’s 405 Freeway near Sepulveda Pass, just to the west of Los Angeles, before workers took it down Tuesday.

value.title: Trump halts COVID-19 relief talks until after election
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump says he has instructed aides to stop negotiating on another round of COVID-19 relief until after the election

value.title: EXCLUSIVE: Former CIA director John Brennan says the biggest threat to the 2020 election is Trump himself
value.excerpt: Russia got everything it could have hoped for from Donald Trump's presidency, the former CIA chief said in an interview.

value.title: Biden with upper-single digit lead over Trump with 4 weeks until Election Day: polls
value.excerpt: With the clock ticking toward Election Day on Nov. 3, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden holds a nearly 10-point lead over President Trump in an average of the latest national polls.

value.title: Coming full circle, Trump returns to false, misguided 'flu' rhetoric
value.excerpt: Nearly seven months after his misguided "think about that!" tweet, comparing COVID-19 to the flue, the Republican has apparently come full circle.

value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely tweets that Covid-19 is less lethal than the flu
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has consistently downplayed the threat of the coronavirus in public, and it seems testing positive for the virus himself has not changed his tune.

value.title: Bernstein on Trump: He has become homicidally negligent
value.excerpt: CNN political analyst Carl Bernstein reacts to the White House declining an offer from the CDC to help contact trace the coronavirus outbreak in the White House.

value.title: Trump deploying 'high-risk strategy' by leaving hospital so early, Rollins says
value.excerpt: The president is deploying a "high-risk strategy" by leaving Walter Reed hospital earlier than expected, Republican strategist Ed Rollins told NYT.

value.title: Michelle Obama releases closing campaign message: Vote for Biden 'like your lives depend on it'
value.excerpt: Former first lady Michelle Obama is making her closing message to Americans in a campaign video released less than one month until Election Day, imploring people to vote as she shares why she believes the stakes are so high this year.
